	   <tr><td colspan=2>Preach it brother! (or sister?)<br><br>I personally far prefer the air pet to water- I find that w/ malise his stuns stop runners better than the earth pet, and deal damage to boot!&nbsp;&nbsp;Unless I'm up against giants, I've always found the airpet's uber AGI (I've actually found my AP's AGI to be better than my FP's, though I may be wrong) will outweigh the EP's Hp's by at LEAST 20%.  Also, not getting hit means less mana wasted on pet heals (but I still keep RE memed).<br><br>The WP has immense application, though I've found it to be pretty specialized, there is no excuse for not having one in your spellbook (yes I met a fool mage who didn't have one a few weeks ago) SR in LGuk is so far where I use WP the most, but plenty of other spots; at level 12 I made a small fortune hunting darkweeds in ecomm with this guy.<br><br>FP:  Will always hold a special place in the hearts of Mages everywhere.  Not only is he the ULTIMATE damage machine, but he is the most closely related to our nukes; the mainstay of magician offensive(sp?) power.  Let's face it, they call us elementalists, but we are really fire-focused.  He also has the only tail of all the magician pets.  Coincidence? I think not!  We are ment for him, He is ment for us, he is the most powerful by far of mage pets, it's only a matter of knowing how to use him right.<br>Also, he keeps us warm on those long Velious trips.  I use my AP more often, but I love my FP more.  He's also got the best focus item;  honestly, the shovel is great fun, but you can't emote that you're lighting the warrior on fire with it (although if your ever in a cave somewhere, whip out the shovel for a sec and /em dug this cave with his/her own two hands!)<br><br>What is the EP? hitpoints. that's all he is, a bundle of hitpoints.  He's a good travel buddy, almost always gives me enough time to mem gate if I forgot before setting out, and buys alot of time to consider the fight and various options.  He's great for dueling tanks who will generally ignore his taunting and go straight for the caster.  But: his root NEVER sticks except on lowish blues and malise victims, he eats heal mana, he has no special skills (terrible singing voice, and can't cast clarity) he tracks dirt everywhere, and to top it all off: he smells bad!  Take a look at him once!  That's not all dirt!<br><br>If you don't agree, then fine, but also I should note that I have an actual disclaimer button for using the earthpet, noting that when the pet roots something in front of a wanderer and causes a 20-mob train(yes, EP causes trains! It takes a lot of work to keep this from happening, and sometimes in  dungeons a caster isn't up to it after a bad fight.), it was the group that wanted root: The mage said AIR!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
